Tested in multiple scenarios.

short_description: OIG - Run the Dynamically Build Audit Triggers SQL in UAT and PROD deployments to ensure VIPAudit table is kept up to date.
description: Can be found in TFS, but copying here just for safekeeping for future project members.-- Reworked a bit, but based on http://weblogs.asp.net/jongalloway/adding-simple-trigger-based-auditing-to-your-sql-server-database-- BGH 04/29/2016-- BGH 11/15/2016 -- Remove/Delete SPs now are passed @CURRENTUSERID and Update the record first. So, now extracting d.ModifiedBy during Auditing of Deletes. Also applies to some XML-based SAVE SPs that handle sub-record deletions as well.-- BGH 01/04/2017 -- Brackets around column names in case they are reserved words. Start Auditing VIPSecurityAccess table because column names are now escaped.---- This routine trades off a bit of performance for a single record for much better performance dealing with multiple updates or deletes.---- TODO: perhaps change "_ChangeTracking" to "Auditing"USE VIPGO-- DEFINE the AUDIT TABLE NAME here!Declare @Audit_Table varchar(100)    SET @Audit_Table = 'VIPAudit' -- Notes, if you change this, you need to also manually change the direct reference to the VIPAudit table in the CREATE TABLE statement below--DEFINE the tables to audit!--Note both a list of excluded and optionally explicitly included tables----Exclude these (must exclude at least one!)DECLARE @ExcludeTableList TABLE (Value VARCHAR(100))    INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('sysdiagrams') -- Do not remove    INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES (@Audit_Table) -- The name of the Audit table    INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPLog') -- The name of the Log table    INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPIDValue')    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPSecurityAccess')    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPConfiguration') -- The name of the Configuration table    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPAnalytics') -- The name of the Analytics table    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPUsers') -- The name of the Users table    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('VIPTables') -- The name of the Tables master table    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList VALUES ('TypeTableLookup') -- The name of the Lookup table    --INSERT INTO @ExcludeTableList... -- add more--Include these (if this table is empty, routine will include ALL TABLES IN DB that are not in the above exclusion list)DECLARE @IncludeTableList TABLE (Value VARCHAR(100))    --INSERT INTO @IncludeTableList VALUES ('EPSManager')    --INSERT INTO @IncludeTableList VALUES ('OperationalDivisionType')    --INSERT INTO @IncludeTableList VALUES ('Investment')    --INSERT INTO @IncludeTableList VALUES ('VIPAnalytics')    --INSERT INTO @IncludeTableList... -- add more--DEFINE Column names to exclude from Audit table (must exclude at least one!)DECLARE @ExcludeColumnList Table (Value varchar(100))    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('Id')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('ID')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('CreatedBy')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('CreatedOn')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('ModifiedBy')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('ModifiedOn')    Insert Into @ExcludeColumnList Values ('Image') -- US7336 - Update Audit SQL to skip VARBINARY type fields (or in the interim, skip columns named Image)/TA13692 - Quick fix: Ignore columns named Image    DECLARE @ExcludeColumns nvarchar(max)    SELECT @ExcludeColumns = (COALESCE(@ExcludeColumns + '''''' + ',''''','') + cast(Value as nvarchar(max)))    FROM @ExcludeColumnList    set @EXCLUDECOLUMNS = '''''' + @EXCLUDECOLUMNS + ''''''--Create Audit Table if it does not exist --IF NOT EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES WHERE TABLE_NAME= @Audit_Table)CREATE TABLE VIPAudit(    Id [bigint] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,    TableName varchar(100) NOT NULL,    FieldId int NOT NULL,    FieldName varchar(100) NOT NULL,    PreviousValue varchar(max) NULL,    NewValue varchar(max) NULL,    ModifiedBy varchar(50),    ModifiedOn datetime not null DEFAULT (GetDate()),    SystemUser varchar(50) not null default ('UNKNOWN'),    AuditType varchar(1) not null default ('X'))-- Loop through all of the tables defined in the database, adding customized audit triggers as defined above --DECLARE @sql nvarchar(max), @TABLE_NAME sysnameDECLARE @ModifiedBy_Placeholder nvarchar(max)SET NOCOUNT ONSELECT @TABLE_NAME= MIN(TABLE_NAME)FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TablesWHERE TABLE_TYPE= 'BASE TABLE' AND (TABLE_NAME NOT IN (SELECT Value FROM @ExcludeTableList)) AND (not exists (select 1 from @IncludeTableList) or (TABLE_NAME IN (SELECT Value FROM @IncludeTableList)))WHILE @TABLE_NAME IS NOT NULL    BEGIN        --We need to bypass querying the ModifiedBy column if it does not exist in the audited table (otherwise updates and/or deletes will fail). It's best to check this at the time we create the trigger vs. every time the trigger runs.        Set @ModifiedBy_Placeholder = 'COALESCE(i.ModifiedBy,d.ModifiedBy)'        IF COL_LENGTH(@TABLE_NAME,'ModifiedBy') IS NULL            BEGIN                Set @ModifiedBy_Placeholder = '''''N/A''''' -- must be literal string reference in the script within a script            END        EXEC('IF OBJECT_ID (''' + @TABLE_NAME+ 'Auditing'', ''TR'') IS NOT NULL DROP TRIGGER ' + @TABLE_NAME+ 'Auditing') -- Removes the old manually created audit trigger if it exists.        EXEC('IF OBJECT_ID (''' + @TABLE_NAME+ 'Audit'', ''TR'') IS NOT NULL DROP TRIGGER ' + @TABLE_NAME+ 'Audit') -- Removes the old manually created audit trigger if it exists (variant of name)        EXEC('IF OBJECT_ID (''' + @TABLE_NAME+ '_ChangeTracking'', ''TR'') IS NOT NULL DROP TRIGGER ' + @TABLE_NAME+ '_ChangeTracking') -- Removes the last version of the audit trigger generated from this code.            SELECT @sql = N'' -- Reset this to the empty string each time through the While loop.            SELECT @sql = @sql +    N'    create trigger ' + @TABLE_NAME+ '_ChangeTracking on ' + @TABLE_NAME+ '    after update, delete--,insert -- we do not want inserts    as        declare        @bit int,        @field int,        @maxfield int,        @char int,        @fieldname varchar(100),        @TableName varchar(100),        @PKCols varchar(1000),        @sql nvarchar(max) = N'''',        @ModifiedOn varchar(21),        @SystemUser varchar(50),        @AuditType char(1),        @PKFieldSelect varchar(1000),        @PKValueSelect varchar(1000)        select @TableName = ''' + @TABLE_NAME+ '''        -- date and user        select @SystemUser = system_user, @ModifiedOn = convert(varchar(8), getdate(), 112) + '' '' + convert(varchar(12), getdate(), 114)        -- Action        if exists (select 1 from inserted)            if exists (select 1 from deleted)                select @AuditType = ''U''            else                select @AuditType = ''I'' -- we do not want inserts        else            select @AuditType = ''D''        -- get list of columns        select * into #ins from inserted        select * into #del from deleted        -- Get primary key columns for full outer join        select @PKCols = coalesce(@PKCols + '' and'', '' on'') + '' i.'' + c.COLUMN_NAME + '' = d.'' + c.COLUMN_NAME        from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS pk, INFORMATION_SCHEMA.KEY_COLUMN_USAGE c        where pk.TABLE_NAME = @TableName and CONSTRAINT_TYPE = ''PRIMARY KEY'' and c.TABLE_NAME = pk.TABLE_NAME and c.CONSTRAINT_NAME = pk.CONSTRAINT_NAME        -- Get primary key fields select for insert        select @PKFieldSelect = coalesce(@PKFieldSelect+''+'','''') + '''''''' + COLUMN_NAME + ''''''''        from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS pk, INFORMATION_SCHEMA.KEY_COLUMN_USAGE c        where pk.TABLE_NAME = @TableName        and CONSTRAINT_TYPE = ''PRIMARY KEY''        and c.TABLE_NAME = pk.TABLE_NAME        and c.CONSTRAINT_NAME = pk.CONSTRAINT_NAME        select @PKValueSelect = coalesce(@PKValueSelect+''+'','''') + ''convert(varchar(100), coalesce(i.'' + COLUMN_NAME + '',d.'' + COLUMN_NAME + ''))''        from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS pk, INFORMATION_SCHEMA.KEY_COLUMN_USAGE c           where pk.TABLE_NAME = @TableName           and CONSTRAINT_TYPE = ''PRIMARY KEY''           and c.TABLE_NAME = pk.TABLE_NAME           and c.CONSTRAINT_NAME = pk.CONSTRAINT_NAME        if @PKCols is null            begin                raiserror(''no PK on table %s'', 16, -1, @TableName)                return            end        select @field = 0, @maxfield = max(ORDINAL_POSITION) from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where TABLE_NAME = @TableName        while @field < @maxfield            begin                select @field = min(ORDINAL_POSITION) from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where TABLE_NAME = @TableName and ORDINAL_POSITION > @field                select @bit = (@field - 1 )% 8 + 1                select @bit = power(2,@bit - 1)                select @char = ((@field - 1) / 8) + 1                if @AuditType in (''I'',''D'') or substring(COLUMNS_UPDATED(),@char, 1) & @bit > 0                    begin                        select @fieldname = COLUMN_NAME from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where TABLE_NAME = @TableName and ORDINAL_POSITION = @field                        select @sql = N''''; -- Reset this to the empty string each time through the While loop.                        select @sql = @sql + N''insert ' + @Audit_Table + ' (AuditType, TableName, FieldId, FieldName, PreviousValue, NewValue, ModifiedBy, ModifiedOn, SystemUser)''                        select @sql = @sql + '' select '''''' + @AuditType + ''''''''                        select @sql = @sql + '','''''' + UPPER(@TableName) + ''''''''                        select @sql = @sql + '',convert(int,'' + @PKValueSelect + '')''                        select @sql = @sql + '','''''' + UPPER(@fieldname) + ''''''''                        select @sql = @sql + '',convert(varchar(1000),coalesce(try_convert(varchar(max),d.['' + @fieldname + '']),''''''''))''                        select @sql = @sql + '',convert(varchar(1000),coalesce(try_convert(varchar(max),i.['' + @fieldname + '']),''''''''))''                        select @sql = @sql + '',convert(varchar(1000),coalesce(' + @ModifiedBy_Placeholder+ ',''''DELETION''''))''                        select @sql = @sql + '','''''' + @ModifiedOn + ''''''''                        select @sql = @sql + '','''''' + @SystemUser + ''''''''                        select @sql = @sql + '' from #ins i full outer join #del d''                        select @sql = @sql + @PKCols                        select @sql = @sql + '' where 1=1''                        select @sql = @sql + '' and (not ('''''' + @fieldname + '''''' in (' + @ExcludeColumns + ')))''                                select @sql = @sql + '' and (i.['' + @fieldname + ''] <> d.['' + @fieldname + '']''                        select @sql = @sql + '' or (i.['' + @fieldname + ''] is null and  d.['' + @fieldname + ''] is not null)''                        select @sql = @sql + '' or (i.['' + @fieldname + ''] is not null and  d.['' + @fieldname + ''] is null))''                        exec (@sql)                    end            end    '        SELECT
